20employees%20to%20gather%20evidence%20and%20seek%20legal%20counsel%20if%20necessary.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20WORLD%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fhow-hot-americano-egg-and-bottle-of-water-cost-a-woman-her-job%2Farticleshow%2F113700169.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Should%20Hindu%20Religious%20Institutions%20Be%20Freed%20From%20State%20Control%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-12%2Fd2dr06r8_pilgrim_625x300_21_December_22.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20extent%20of%20government%20involvement%20in%20administering%20temple%20wealth%20has%20been%20a%20deeply%20debated%20topic%20in%20the%20nation's%20religious%20and%20cultural%20ethos.%20Recent%20controversies%2C%20such%20as%20the%20discovery%20of%20beef%20and%20fish%20oil%20in%20the%20sacred%20Tirupati%20Laddu%2C%20have%20brought%20the%20debate%20over%20government%20control%20of%20temple%20wealth%20back%20into%20the%20spotlight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstitutions%20like%20the%20Tirumala%20Tirupati%20Devasthanams%20(TTD)%2C%20Kerala's%20Sabarimala%20Temple%2C%20and%20Maharashtra's%20Shirdi%20Sai%20Baba%20Temple%20consistently%20receive%20substantial%20donations%2C%20making%20them%20some%20of%20the%20wealthiest%20religious%20establishments%20in%20the%20world.%20Beyond%20donations%2C%20temples%20also%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20boosting%20religious%20tourism%2C%20which%20contributes%20to%20regional%20economies.%20A%202016%20study%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Policy%20Studies%20estimated%20that%20the%20wealth%20held%20by%20major%20Hindu%20temples%20could%20be%20as%20high%20as%20%E2%82%B95%20lakh%20crore.%20Furthermore%2C%20a%202019%20study%20by%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Public%20Finance%20and%20Policy%20(NIPFP)%20revealed%20that%20religious%20tourism%20-%20mainly%20Hindu%20pilgrimages%20-%20contributes%20around%202.32%25%20to%20India's%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERoots%20In%20British%20Colonial%20Rule%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20Tirumala%20Tirupati%20Devasthanams%20(TTD)%2C%20one%20of%20India's%20wealthiest%20temples%2C%20generates%20annual%20revenues%20of%20%E2%82%B93%2C000-%E2%82%B94%2C000%20crore.%20Since%20it%20was%20brought%20under%20state%20control%20in%201933%2C%20TTD's%20cumulative%20revenue%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20around%20%E2%82%B91.8-%E2%82%B92%20lakh%20crore.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20Sabarimala%20Temple%2C%20under%20government%20control%20since%201950%2C%20earns%20approximately%20%E2%82%B9200-%E2%82%B9250%20crore%20annually%2C%20adding%20up%20to%20%E2%82%B913%2C000-%E2%82%B916%2C000%20crore%20over%20the%20last%2074%20years.%20The%20Shirdi%20Sai%20Baba%20Temple%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20controlled%20by%20the%20state%20since%201922%2C%20generates%20around%20%E2%82%B9300%20crore%20annually%2C%20with%20a%20cumulative%20revenue%20of%20%E2%82%B929%2C000%20crore%20over%20102%20years.%20These%20numbers%20highlight%20the%20immense%20financial%20influence%20of%20these%20temples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20origins%20of%20state%20control%20over%20temples%20can%20be%20traced%20back%20to%20British%20colonial%20rule.%20The%20British%20recognised%20the%20immense%20economic%20power%20of%20Hindu%20temples%20and%20took%20steps%20to%20manage%20their%20administration%20to%20ensure%20that%20temple%20revenues%20were%20safeguarded%20and%20used%20for%20their%20colonial%20goals.%20Once%20under%20government%20intervention%2C%20temples%20that%20had%20been%20traditionally%20managed%20by%20religious%20bodies%20were%20overseen%20by%20state%20authorities-a%20trend%20that%20persisted%20even%20after%20India's%20independence%20in%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20dismantling%20this%20colonial%20system%20of%20control%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20expanded%20its%20oversight.%20Laws%20like%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Hindu%20Religious%20and%20Charitable%20Endowments%20Act%20of%201959%20formalised%20state%20control%2C%20giving%20governments%20the%20authority%20to%20appoint%20trustees%2C%20manage%20temple%20properties%2C%20and%20direct%20how%20temple%20funds%20should%20be%20spent.%20The%20intention%20was%20to%20prevent%20mismanagement%20and%20corruption%20and%20ensure%20that%20temple%20wealth%20was%20used%20for%20public%20welfare%2C%20particularly%20in%20education%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Wide%20Debate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20intervention%20has%20sparked%20significant%20controversy.%20Many%20argue%20that%20state%20control%20over%20Hindu%20temples%20is%20discriminatory%2C%20raising%20questions%20about%20religious%20freedom%20and%20equality%20before%20the%20law.%20While%20Hindu%20temples%20are%20subject%20to%20strict%20government%20oversight%2C%20religious%20institutions%20belonging%20to%20other%20communities-such%20as%20mosques%20and%20churches-enjoy%20considerable%20financial%20autonomy.%20For%20example%2C%20mosques%20are%20managed%20by%20the%20Waqf%20Board%2C%20and%20churches%20are%20overseen%20by%20diocesan%20authorities%2C%20both%20of%20which%20control%20their%20assets%20without%20government%20interference-a%20privilege%20Hindu%20temples%20do%20not%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20disparity%20has%20led%20to%20growing%20calls%20for%20the%20autonomy%20of%20Hindu%20temples.%20Critics%20argue%20that%20temple%20revenues%2C%20being%20religious%20donations%2C%20should%20be%20managed%20by%20the%20community%20itself%2C%20rather%20than%20by%20the%20state.%20They%20claim%20that%20government%20involvement%20in%20temple%20administration%20violates%20Article%2025%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20which%20guarantees%20freedom%20of%20religion.%20Hindu%20leaders%20and%20devotees%20have%20challenged%20state%20control%20of%20temple%20finances%20in%20court%20on%20several%20occasions%2C%20though%20judicial%20rulings%20have%20largely%20upheld%20the%20state's%20right%20to%20intervene.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20is%20not%20just%20a%20legal%20or%20constitutional%20one%3B%20it%20is%20also%20politically%20sensitive.%20Many%20Hindu%20groups%20believe%20that%20the%20state's%20control%20of%20temple%20revenues%20reflects%20an%20inherent%20bias%20against%20the%20majority%20religion%20in%20what%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20secular%20democracy.%20They%20question%20why%20Hindu%20institutions%20are%20subject%20to%20government%20oversight%20while%20religious%20institutions%20of%20minority%20communities%20are%20left%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStriking%20A%20Balance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobally%2C%20most%20religious%20institutions%20enjoy%20financial%20autonomy.%20In%20the%20United%20States%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20religious%20organisations%20-%20whether%20churches%2C%20temples%2C%20mosques%2C%20or%20synagogues%20-%20are%20tax-exempt%20and%20manage%20their%20finances%20independently.%20The%20same%20holds%20in%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20where%20religious%20institutions%20control%20their%20revenues%20without%20state%20intervention.%20India's%20approach%20to%20temple%20management%20is%20therefore%20unique%2C%20raising%20questions%20about%20whether%20the%20state%20truly%20maintains%20a%20secular%20stance%20in%20dealing%20with%20different%20religions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20the%20complexities%20of%20this%20issue%20requires%20a%20deep%20look%20into%20India's%20colonial%20history%2C%20post-independence%20policies%2C%20and%20the%20delicate%20balance%20between%20religion%20and%20state.%20As%20renowned%20advocate%20Fali%20S.%20Nariman%20once%20said%2C%20*%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20state%20may%20regulate%20secular%20activities%2C%20the%20moment%20it%20interferes%20with%20the%20religious%20essence%20of%20an%20institution%2C%20it%20steps%20onto%20dangerous%20ground%20where%20constitutional%20rights%20can%20be%20trampled.%26quot%3B*%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENariman's%20warning%20remains%20particularly%20relevant%20today%2C%20as%20the%20debate%20over%20temple%20control%20continues%20to%20raise%20concerns%20about%20religious%20freedom%20and%20equality.%20In%20a%20world%20where%20religious%20institutions%20are%20generally%20allowed%20to%20manage%20their%20own%20finances%20and%20assets%2C%20the%20question%20persists%3A%20why%20should%20Hindu%20temples%20in%20India%20not%20be%20granted%20the%20same%20autonomy%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Anurag%20Punetha%20is%20a%20Senior%20Broadcast%20Journalist%20and%20Head%20of%20Media%20at%20IGNCA.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727349720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-12%2Fd2dr06r8_pilgrim_625x300_21_December_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fis-it-time-to-free-hindu-religious-institutions-from-state-control-6654826%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20Hindu%20temples%20are%20subject%20to%20strict%20government%20oversight%2C%20religious%20institutions%20belonging%20to%20other%20communities-such%20as%20mosques%20and%20churches-enjoy%20considerable%20financial%20autonomy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ED%20seizes%20properties%20of%20Elvish%20Yadav%20and%20Fazilpuria%20in%20money%20laundering%20case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727349262000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113701196%2Cimgsize-1226613.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fhindi%2Fed-takes-serious-action-against-elvish-yadav-and-fazilpuria-in-mon