20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20relief%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20their%20safety.%20A%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheharrispoll.com%2Fbriefs%2Flocation-sharing-features%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoll%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20The%20Harris%20Poll%20and%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20found%20that%20one%20in%20six%20respondents%20reported%20always%20having%20location%20sharing%20turned%20on%2C%20and%2037%25%20of%20those%20who%20said%20they%20used%20location-sharing%20apps%20(like%20Find%20My)%20said%20doing%20so%20made%20them%20feel%20safer.%20Just%20last%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flife360-family-safety-app-sells-user-location-data-report-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELife360%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20prominent%20tracking%20apps%2C%20reported%2050%20million%20monthly%20active%20users%2C%20with%20downloads%20in%20the%20US%20doubling%20since%202021%20as%20it%20gained%20popularity%20among%20Gen%20Zers.%20And%20increasingly%2C%20safety%20concerns%20are%20extending%20up%20a%20generation%20%E2%80%94%20kids%20are%20now%20concerned%20about%20their%20parents%20rather%20than%20just%20the%20other%20way%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20West%20Virginia%2C%20Kacy%20Shafer%20had%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20protective%26quot%3B%20parents%2C%20she%20said.%20She%20was%20an%20only%20child%20and%20her%20dad%20served%20in%20the%20military%2C%20so%20it%20was%20mostly%20her%20mother%20who%20laid%20down%20the%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wasn't%20allowed%20to%20just%20go%20have%20playdates%20wherever%20I%20wanted%20%E2%80%94%20she%20had%20to%20call%20the%20parents%2C%20make%20sure%20they%20would%20be%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Shafer%2C%20who%20is%2029%2C%20said.%20While%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgabb-smartphone-review-teens-kids-social-media-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephones%20lacked%20tracking%20technology%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20Shafer%20was%20younger%2C%20her%20parents%20set%20hard%20limits%20on%20which%20hours%20she%20could%20use%20her%20first%20cellphone%20and%20whom%20she%20could%20contact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20as%20an%20adult%2C%20Shafer%20tracks%20her%20mom's%20phone.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20funny%20how%20the%20tables%20have%20turned%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20As%20her%2061-year-old%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emom%20has%20gotten%20older%2C%20checking%20where%20she%20is%20at%20least%20once%20a%20day%20offers%20some%20%26quot%3Bpeace%20of%20mind%2C%26quot%3B%20Shafer%20says.%20Her%20mother%20doesn't%20mind%20the%20tracking.%20In%20fact%2C%20they%20check%20in%20on%20each%20other%20and%20joke%20about%20it%20a%20lot.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%2C%20I%20just%20check%20to%20see%20where%20she's%20at%2C%20and%20I'm%20like%3A%20'Hey%2C%20are%20you%20at%20the%20store%3F%20Can%20you%20grab%20me%20this%3F'%26quot%3B%20Shafer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephiney%20Foley%2C%2037%2C%20also%20had%20strict%20parents.%20Her%20family%20immigrated%20to%20New%20York%20from%20Shanghai%20when%20she%20was%208.%20She%20described%20her%20mom%20and%20dad's%20parenting%20style%20as%20%26quot%3Bvery%20typical%20of%20overbearing%20parents%2C%20especially%20immigrant%20parents.%26quot%3B%20Tracking%20technology%20wasn't%20around%20when%20Foley%20was%20a%20teen%2C%20but%20her%20parents%20still%20kept%20a%20close%20eye.%20%26quot%3BMy%20mom%20is%20constantly%20on%20my%20back%20looking%20over%20my%20shoulders%20doing%20things%2C%20even%20when%20I%20was%20in%20high%20school%2C%26quot%3B%20Foley%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Shafer%2C%20Foley%20now%20tracks%20her%20parents%2C%20who%20are%20in%20their%2060s%20and%2070s.%20It's%20typically%20a%20safety%20precaution%20when%20they%20travel.%20One%20time%20her%20mother%20got%20lost%20driving%20her%20RV%20in%20the%20Great%20Smoky%20Mountains%20in%20Tennessee%20and%20Foley%20was%20able%20to%20help%20her%20navigate%20out%20of%20the%20park.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20roles%20are%20kind%20of%20reversed%20now%20in%20a%20way%20that%20I%20am%20kind%20of%20the%20parent%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Tracking%20allows%20Foley%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Seattle%2C%20to%20feel%20more%20connected%20to%20her%20Florida-based%20parents%20and%20feel%20empowered%20to%20help%20in%20emergencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelley%20Roebuck%2C%20a%2046-year-old%20living%20in%20Illinois%2C%20installed%20a%20tracking%20app%20on%20her%20son's%20phone%20when%20he%20was%20in%20junior%20high%20school%20to%20know%20his%20whereabouts%20after%20he%20lost%20his%20phone%20twice.%20At%20first%2C%20it%20was%20just%20a%20way%20to%20keep%20track%20of%20his%20phone%2C%20but%20it's%20since%20morphed%20into%20a%20more%20central%20part%20of%20their%20lives.%20Her%20son%2C%20now%2020%2C%20tracks%20her%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20day%2C%20I%20didn't%20come%20straight%20home%20and%20he%20called%20me%2C%20'Mom%2C%20what%20are%20you%20doing%20at%20Cousin%20Erica's%20house%3F'%26quot%3B%20Roebuck%20told%20me.%20She%20described%20her%20son%2C%20who%20is%20also%20her%20only%20child%2C%20as%20%26quot%3Bvery%20protective%20of%20his%20friends%20and%20family.%26quot%3B%20When%20she%20used%20to%20go%20out%20of%20town%20often%2C%20he%20would%20check%20in%20when%20he%20didn't%20see%20her%20at%20the%20hotel%20or%20her%20friend's%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoebuck%20and%20her%20son%20now%20track%20each%20other%20%26quot%3Bevenly.%26quot%3B%20When%20he%20is%20out%20late%2C%20she%20wants%20to%20make%20sure%20he's%20in%20a%20safe%20place.%20Even%20her%20son's%20best%20friend%2C%20whom%20Roebuck%20considers%20her%20%26quot%3Bbonus%20son%2C%26quot%3B%20wanted%20to%20share%20locations%20with%20her%2C%20so%20he%20was%20added%20to%20their%20Life360%20plan%20in%20high%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20later%2C%20her%20son's%20friend%20called%20Roebuck%20when%20she%20was%20out%20late%20to%20check%20in%20on%20her.%20When%20she%20asked%20how%20he%20knew%20where%20she%20was%2C%20he%20reminded%20her%20he%20had%20the%20tracker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20I%20forget%20y'all%20still%20had%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Roebuck%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20adult%20children%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-happy-parents-tracking-location-apps-life360-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneutral%20views%20on%20being%20tracked%20by%20their%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20they%20were%20younger.%20Gabrielle%20Lask%2C%20a%2025-year-old%20only%20child%2C%20has%20been%20tracked%20by%20her%20mother%20since%20she%20got%20an%20iPhone%20at%20age%2013.%20Though%20she%20said%20her%20mom%20was%20acting%20out%20of%20love%20and%20concern%2C%20she%20also%20described%20being%20tracked%20as%20%26quot%3Bincredibly%20annoying%20and%2C%20at%20times%2C%20a%20total%20invasion%20of%20privacy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20a%20very%20good%20kid%2C%20very%20trustworthy%2C%26quot%3B%20Lask%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BShe%20just%20has%20really%20bad%20anxiety.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELask%20described%20her%20mom%20as%20very%20overprotective%3B%20she%20would%20often%20text%20her%20about%20her%20whereabouts%20and%20what%20she%20was%20doing%20even%20though%20she%20was%20also%20tracking%20her%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20she%20is%20older%20and%20living%20independently%2C%20Lask%20has%20started%20to%20push%20back.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20using%20this%20as%20a%20safety%20mechanism%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20recalled%20telling%20her%20mom%20a%20few%20years%20ago%20when%20she%20was%20really%20upset.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20using%20it%20as%20an%20invasion%20of%20privacy.%26quot%3B%20Lask%20temporarily%20blocked%20her%20mom%20from%20seeing%20her%20location%2C%20which%20she%20said%20made%20her%20mom%20%26quot%3Bfreak%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20basically%20said%2C%20'I%20will%20put%20you%20back%2C%20but%20this%20cannot%20continue%2C'%26quot%3B%20Lask%20said.%20%26quot%3B'You%20have%20to%20use%20it%20as%20what%20it's%20meant%20to%20be%20used%20for.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20excessive%20concern%20didn't%20get%20passed%20down%20to%20Lask.%20She%20doesn't%20track%20her%20mom's%20location%20%E2%80%94%20and%20she%20doesn't%20have%20much%20interest%20in%20knowing%20it.%20%26quot%3BShe%20doesn't%20go%20out%20much%2C%20and%20if%20she%20does%2C%20trust%20and%20believe%2C%20she%20is%20texting%20and%20calling%20me%20nonstop%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20worry%20about%20her%20because%20she%20worries%20about%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Kanchi%20Wijesekera%2C%20a%20clinical%20psychologist%20in%20California%2C%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelicopter-parent-son-went-college-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelicopter%20parenting%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20methods%20like%20intensive%20tracking%20makes%20kids%20feel%20%26quot%3Bsuffocating%20and%20that%20parents%20do%20not%20trust%20them.%26quot%3B%20She%20said%20it%20could%20ultimately%20add%20strain%20to%20the%20relationship%20as%20kids%20grow%20older%20and%20start%20setting%20boundaries.%20If%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20and%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20don't%20feel%20listened%20to%2C%20it%20can%20drive%20a%20wedge%20between%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20though%2C%20those%20conversations%20can%20be%20transformative%20in%20a%20positive%20way.%20When%20Julianne%20Goldfinger%20was%2015%2C%20her%20mom%20ordered%20paper%20copies%20of%20her%20texts%20from%20their%20cell%20provider.%20Her%20mom%20had%20been%20worried%20about%20how%20little%20she%20knew%20about%20Goldfinger's%20life%20now%20that%20she%20silently%20texted%20her%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20still%20felt%20like%20an%20invasion%20of%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20old%20enough%20when%20she%20did%20that%20to%20kind%20of%20push%20back%20at%20her%20and%20say%2C%20'You%20really%20broke%20my%20trust%20here%2C'%26quot%3B%20Goldfinger%2C%20now%2035%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20%E2%80%94%20my%20mom%20realizing%20that%20I%20was%20growing%20up%20and%20needed%20some%20space.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldfinger%20and%20her%20parents%20now%20track%20each%20other's%20locations%20when%20they%20respectively%20travel%2C%20which%20doesn't%20bother%20her%20since%20she's%20been%20able%20to%20have%20open%20conversations%20with%20her%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20really%20come%20to%20find%20my%20mom%20to%20be%20more%20of%20my%20friend%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldfinger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20parents%20and%20their%20adult%20kids%20are%20staying%20in%20closer%20contact%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Ffamily%2Farchive%2F2024%2F07%2Fmodern-parenting-grown-children%2F678942%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethan%20generations%20past%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2024%2F01%2F25%2Fparents-young-adult-children-and-the-transition-to-adulthood%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20January%20found%20that%20over%2070%25%20of%20respondents%20with%20children%20ages%2018%20to%2034%20reported%20speaking%20with%20their%20kids%20at%20least%20a%20few%20times%20a%20week%20on%20the%20phone.%20And%20more%20parents%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2024%2F09%2F04%2Fus-news%2Fnext-level-helicopter-parents-track-their-adult-children-interfere-in-roommate-conflicts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etracking%20their%20kids%20in%20college%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20quell%20their%20anxiety%20about%20the%20separation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20big%20shift%20from%20the%20weekly%20or%20monthly%20check-in%20phone%20calls%20that%20ruled%20parent-child%20relationships%20in%20the%20past.%20But%20many%20families%20like%20the%20extra%20interaction.%20For%20more%20people%2C%20location%20sharing%20is%20simply%20a%20way%20to%20stay%20connected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Howard%20got%20over%20the%20initial%20shock%20of%20being%20tracked%20without%20her%20consent%2C%20she%20started%20to%20understand%20the%20appeal%20of%20the%20tech%20and%20began%20following%20her%20children's%20locations%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20one%20daughter%2C%20she%20went%20out%20of%20town%20just%20a%20couple%20of%20weeks%20ago%2C%20and%20I'm%20watching%20her%20come%20down%20I-75%2C%20and%20I'm%20thinking%20in%20my%20mind%2C%20'She's%20driving%20awfully%20fast%2C'%26quot%3B%20Howard%20said.%20She%20added%20that%20the%20mutual%20tracking%20gives%20her%20peace%20of%20mind%20that%20her%20kids%20aren't%20in%20danger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWijesekera%20said%20that%20attitudes%20around%20tracking%20are%20shaped%20by%20trust%20and%20communication.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20have%20a%20really%20close%20bond%2C%20it's%20easier%20to%20see%20those%20behaviors%20from%20a%20well-intentioned%20place%20versus%20a%20sign%20of%20their%20lack%20of%20trust%20and%20wanting%20to%20hover%20and%20force%20their%20decisions%20on%20us.%26quot%3B%20Kids%20who%20grew%20up%20being%20accountable%20for%20their%20whereabouts%20don't%20necessarily%20look%20back%20on%20the%20memory%20negatively%2C%20so%20long%20as%20they%20feel%20their%20parents%20trusted%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20certainly%20true%20for%20Joy%20Loverde.%20The%2072-year-old%20shares%20and%20tracks%20locations%20with%20both%20her%2049-year-old%20daughter%20and%20her%20two%20adult%20grandchildren.%20%26quot%3BWe%20jumped%20on%20it%20early%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Loverde%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Illinois%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20wanting%20to%20remain%20even%20closer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELoverde%20raised%20her%20only%20daughter%20on%20her%20own%2C%20and%20they've%20stayed%20very%20close%20%E2%80%94%20now%20Loverde%2C%20her%20daughter%2C%20and%20her%20daughter's%20daughter%20all%20track%20one%20another.%20They%20do%20it%20partly%20to%20check%20in%2C%20and%20partly%20just%20to%20know%20more%20about%20one%20another's%20lives.%20%26quot%3BWe%20laugh%20%E2%80%94%20we%20think%20it's%20really%20funny%2C%26quot%3B%20Loverde%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20poking%20in%20and%20out%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20families%20like%20theirs%2C%20it's%20simply%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20love%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjulia-pugachevsky%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJulia%20Pugachevsky%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20health%20reporter%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-tracking-parents-location-sharing-phones-helicopter-parenting-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727343602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f186b7d17aa3c7b2b4f5ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-tracking-parents-location-sharing-phones-helicopter-parenting-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Now%20that%20they're%20grown%20up%2C%20the%20children%20of%20helicopter%20parents%20are%20using%20location-sharing%20apps%20to%20keep%20tabs%20on%20their%20parents.%20It's%20the%20new%20family%20norm.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpugachevsky%40insider.com%20(Julia%20Pugachevsky)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A65%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-tracking-parents-location-sharing-phones-helicopter-parenting-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20surfer%20without%20a%20degree%20is%20worth%20%2416%20billion%20after%20his%20biotech%20company's%20stock%20soared%201%2C100%25%20in%20a%20year%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Summit%20Therapeutics%20CEO%20Bob%20Duggan%20sh